properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Dangerous wind chill values near -45 are still occurring in a few locales. Wind chill values will dip to the -45 to -50 range again overnight and into Thursday morning. Regions near Hudson Bay may also reach the -45 to -50 range Thursday night. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Risks are greater for young children, older adults, people with chronic illnesses, people working or exercising outdoors, and those without proper shelter. Watch for cold related symptoms: shortness of breath, chest pain, muscle pain and weakness, numbness and colour change in fingers and toes. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Snow Squall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Periods of brief but intense snowfall are occurring. Visibilities will be rapidly reduced due to the heavy snow combined with blowing snow. A snow squall is occurring along a sharp cold front. This cold front is moving southeastward and is currently located from Ramore to Lake Superior National Park. It is expected to reach Earlton to Batchawana Bay Provincial Park near 7:00 PM EST. Snowfall accumulations up to 5 centimetres are possible by the time the cold front passes. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility in some locations. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

Conditions will moderate somewhat during the day Thursday. However, extreme wind chills are expected again Thursday night and Friday morning in areas near Hudson Bay and in the Webequie, Big Trout Lake and Sachigo Lake regions. ### Extreme cold warnings are issued when very cold temperatures or wind chill creates an elevated risk to health such as frost bite and hypothermia. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Blowing Snow Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Poor visibility in snow and blowing snow is expected or occurring in some locations. Total snowfall: near 5 cm. Maximum wind gusts: southwesterly 80 km/h. Locations: Port Saunders and the Straits. Time span: early Thursday morning until Thursday afternoon. ### Visibility may be significantly and suddenly reduced to near zero. Blowing snow advisories are issued when winds are expected to create blowing snow giving poor visibility to 800 metres or less for at least 3 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A period of very cold wind chills is expected. Increasing northwesterly winds combined with temperatures in the minus thirties will bring extremely cold windchill values of minus 50 or lower to the Iqaluit region overnight into Thursday morning. These extreme values will moderated slightly Thursday afternoon but will likely return Thursday night. In addition to the extreme wind chills, winds gusting at times to 60 km/h will also bring blowing snow to the region giving reduced visibilities. These winds are expected to subside Thursday evening. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A period of very cold wind chills continues. The coldest wind chill values will be between minus 40 and minus 45. Extreme cold conditions may still occur in the early part of the evening for Fort Chipewyan. However, temperatures will warm overnight. ### Watch for cold related symptoms: shortness of breath, chest pain, muscle pain and weakness, numbness and colour change in fingers and toes. Extreme cold warnings are issued when very cold temperatures or wind chill creates an elevated risk to health such as frost bite and hypothermia. properties.Title: Snow Squall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Periods of brief but intense snowfall are occurring. Visibilities will be rapidly reduced due to the heavy snow combined with blowing snow. Snowfall amounts of 5 to 10 cm are possible by the time the cold front departs later this afternoon. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility in some locations.
